attributes.descriptionHtml:
Bea is about 14 years old, is up to date on shots and good with women and other dogs and cats. She currently weighs 36 pounds. Her owner passed away and we brought Bea into the rescue when the shelter reached out asking for help. Bea had enlarged mammary glands and her uterus removed once in our care. She is now relaxing in her foster home and living life to its fullest. If you would like to adopt Bea, please put your application in here: http://www.rescuedogsrocknyc.org/general-application. 

RDR's adoption fees include the cost of spay/neuter/microchip at an RDR-approved facility, whether completed before adoption or if deferred because the pet is too young or has a medical issue.  All pets are also current on age-appropriate vaccines at the time of adoption

Given technical constraints on this database, this pet's location may not be as listed here. We can, however, provide transport support for pets in foster at a considerable distance from the adopter.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Who would love a quiet afternoon with you gardening in the shire and be ready on a moments notice to accompany you on a grand adventure? Samwise, of course! Sam is earnest, rustic almost, and he wears his heart of gold on his sleeve. Sam will look to you to be his leader and he will be the secret strength that carries you though even the toughest of days. His resilient spirit has allowed him to travel from humble beginnings with no place of his own to winning the hearts of the rescue volunteers who have been teaching him the ways of people and the comforts of home. Imagine the joy of never having to feel guilty knowing that your best friend would rather to be home with you than at the dog park.

Sam is now looking for his forever place in the country with a fenced yard, quiet surroundings, and an experienced dog lover who prefers the road less traveled for times when a hike is the order of the day. How much fun will it will be walking the solitary back roads on a Tuesday morning at 10 when everyone else is… well... too busy to seize the warm sunny moment you’ll share.

Sam is housebroken, crate trained, knows sit, and certainly knows breakfast and dinner routines. He enthusiastically loves to lean-in and he is a first class snuggler who will not be shy about joining you on the sofa to savor a movie… or three. Sam is ready for the unconditional love of a friend who will teach him even more about the ways of people. In return he will promise to do his very best to listen to your stories, his eyes meeting yours in agreement that life’s journey is difficult and worthy and fun and glorious but not all at once. All the while Sam will share with you the rewards of investing in love.

FENCE REQUIREMENT:  Sam is going to need a yard with a privacy fence that is at least 4 foot high.  

 

If you are interested in Sam, please contact:

rorrcanine@gmail.com    

*** Click here to sponsor this dog! ***

attributes.descriptionHtml:
MEET ANNABELLE aka Hurricane Annie!!! She loves to play with humans of all ages -- and she can play until she drops! She is quirky, funny, and spunky. Annie is a very smart girl who is eager to please and learns quickly.  She has a sweet personality and is a total spaz. Annie is a funny girl who also loves to snuggle.  She's house-trained, crate-trained, and is learning basic obedience commands.

Annabelle's favorite game is "Floor is lava" where she jumps from couch to couch in excitement, and she LOVES to trick you out of the Lazyboy chair so she can sneak onto it and fall asleep. Annabelle would be a great running buddy and will keep you laughing for hours on end if you adopt this unpredictable bundle of crazy joy!

Annabelle will do best in a home with older kids, as she is a larger dog and could have a tendency to knock little ones down accidentally.  If you would like to meet ANNABELLE, please visit our website for our application www.underdogaz.com or email us for more info at info@underdogaz.com

If you would like to meet Annabelle, please visit our website for our adoption application, www.underdogaz.com or send email to info@underdogaz.com

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Donny is very sweet but gets very verbal and loud when telling you that he wants your attention, but he doesn’t want to be snuggled. And if he has something to say he will trot right up to you and carry-on a conversation and when he has said his piece just walks away.

He is calm and friendly and is never aggressive with any other pet family members and he nurtures and grooms his favorite elderly cat.

At night if he sleeps close to your head he will reach his paw out to touch you while you fall asleep and then moves to sleep on your legs or hips. His fur is very soft like a bunny.

Donny likes to jump to high places and back down. He will even jump on your back and use you as a bridge to get somewhere else.  

If Donny is of interest please email and share about yourself and others in the home as well as other pets. He will be happy in a home without children but other cats would be fine.

Donny is being cared for by Community Animal Network, a non-profit organization founded by DiAnna Pfaff-Martin in 1996. C.A.N is a veterinary medical rescue that prepares dogs and cats for forever homes.  

To donate to help cats like Buddy, use our PayPal link: www.PayPal.Me/CommunityAnimal Or Mail checks to: Community Animal Network P.O. Box 8662 Newport Beach, CA 92658

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Meet Tarzan - he is a handsome hound mix looking for his true forever home. Tarzan is a long & leggy guy who is around 65 pounds. He is a sweet boy who loves to give his foster human a hug & enjoys cuddling. He is house-trained, neutered & up to date on all vet care. Tarzan has some anxiety & needs time to warm up to strangers, especially men. Patience, love & commitment will be the key for Tarzan - & a bit of medication (he takes daily meds & does better on it than off). Tarzan generally likes other dogs but has shown some territorial issues lately so being the only dog in the home might be ideal. It seems he plays well outside of the home or on neutral turf more so than inside the home. 
 Tarzan needs a furever person who is patient & dedicated to him for all of his life - dedicated to his somewhat shy nature, dedicated to seeking training & to whatever his care entails. He has been at his foster home a long time so any change will be an adjustment. Potential adopters should be prepared for that.
As his foster mom, I envision his ideal home as one with someone who is fairly settled in life - maybe a single lady (he loves the ladies) who isn't necessarily a homebody, but isn't someone who is gone all the time or entertaining a lot of new people frequently. He is doing great in his crate now when I have to leave him. A couch & bed that will fit both you & Tarzan is a requirement (he is a bed hog - lol). A fenced yard would be great but not a necessity - he isn't ultra-energetic but likes the safety of a yard. He attempts a game of fetch as well but is still working on giving the ball back so I can throw it again. He walks really well on a leash or harness. He has completed some training & his general manners are pretty good. Cats are a no for him. He really is such a loving boy who enjoys snuggles & belly rubs. He deserves the best life in a furever home. Could YOU be his pawfect match?

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Welcome to Cats Meow Dogs Bark Rescue, is an all volunteer animal welfare and rescue organization! Animals listed on our websites and other adoptable websites are available for adoption at our adoption house; Pounce & Fetch (512 Southview Blvd South St. Paul, MN 55075), we have no set hours, but we are always there cleaning and caring for the animals that reside at Pounce & Fetch! Please be aware of our sign on our front door. It will ask that you "Please knock, we are here cleaning" when you are more then welcome to come in and help us and visit the animals. Should it read "We are closed" means that we are not ready to receive guests and perhaps call to schedule at time or wait till the sign is flipped.

To start the journey of adopting a new family member from Cats Meow Dogs Bark Rescue you'll need to complete our adoption application. It is the first step toward possibly adding a new member to your family. You can either stop in at Pounce & Fetch to pick up and complete it or email us at adoptablepets@aol.com and we will send you the form, please complete and return via email.  Unanswered question could delay your application. Please don't be intimidated by our Adoption Application, its purpose in genuine. We have kept it simple for a reason so that we can get to know you and your family so that we can assist you with finding the right pet to join your family, forever! Please note that we are an all volunteer animal rescue and welfare organization, and there may be times where we may have to reschedule (several times too) the Meet & Greets, visiting at Pounce & Fetch as well as Home Visits. We so appreciate your understand and patience.

We are excited to assist you in your search and adoption of your new family member! Don't forget we are always seeking donations so that we can help the animals we rescue and save each and everyday! Please donate NOW so we can help them today! 651-888-2469 or 651-343-1964

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Polly is a sweet energetic girl who is about 4 years old and 55 pounds. She is deaf and was adopted as a puppy. She is crate trained and house broken. She needs a home with a safe fence and older children who can understand that she can't hear them. Polly would be overwhelming for smaller children. Polly can be very picky about her dog friends so she would do best as an only pet. She is a very smart girl and has learned sign language just like humans. She knows sit, stay, down, potty, crate and other commands in sign language. Polly would do well in a home with people willing to spend some time on training each day as she is very eager to learn new things.

~Adoption donation $250. All vetting is up to date. Microchipped and spayed. Also on flea/tick and heartworm preventative. Visit www.ruffloverescue.com/adoption to make this pup a member of your family.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Cassandra is a medium hair grey and white female cat who came from AHS.  Her owner surrendered her.  Cassandra's attitude is still there, she did lash out at Judy after too much petting but not aggressively. She is adjusting finally to being a house cat. Judy says she has bonded and is more comfortable with her and even ventured to Judy's bed to sleep with her. Her name is now Missy and likes the new food she is eating, Sheba and some dry food but not much. She prefers wet food over dry. Right now her favorite place to relax is a plastic bin in the kitchen and loves her toy ball on the cat tree. She is at her forever home, never to come back to a shelter.

She was returned due to her aggressive behavior 6/3/2021

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Icy is a pretty petite senior girl who is 8 years old and a DRM Alumni.  She has not had the easiest life, and has found herself looking for a forever home once again, she needs a forever family who has strong dobe experience.  Icy has a sweet disposition, very loving and attentive to her people, if they are confident owners.   She loves people once she gets to know them on her terms, but she can be spunky and a little pushy with strangers so a slow introduction is best for this girl.  Icy has great house manners and is crate trained.  Icy is not always good with other dogs in the home, as she is the alpha.  She requires a fenced in yard as she isn't always tolerant of dogs she does not know, and little people can scare her.  Icy would enjoy a quiet home where she can lay in the sun, lounge and steal snuggles when she wants them.

This fabulous foster is a Doberman Rescue Minnesota foster dog.

Please read all adoption steps and policies carefully on our website. http://dobermanrescueminnesota.com/adoption-steps/

Qualified adopters are within the approved adoption area, and Adopter will be requested to visit this foster dog at the foster family home. Our foster families are generally located within a 250 mile radius of Minneapolis, MN.

All DRM dogs are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, health checked, microchipped, dewormed, 4DX tested, and on monthly flea/tick and heartworm prevention.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Hi there! My name is Cali. I'm a tortoiseshell cat who loves her markings - the right side of my face is truly a burst of sunshine. I am a more independent girl who's looking for a home that appreciates my expressive personality and can help me blossom into the playful and sweet kitty that I am. Wand toys are my favorite, and I've been known to bunk with other kitties at the shelter. I'd do great if your home already has a cat - that means more friends for me!

I'm a little bit shy at first and would appreciate an owner with a gentle, calm demeanor, and once we've spent some time together, I promise we'll be bonded for life. Come see me and make me yours!

attributes.descriptionHtml: Hey there - I'm Stewart. Yes, I'm fluffy and I'm a big boy! Here's my story, grab a Snickers. So I'm minding my own business, being a cat and everything and the next thing I know, I've got a booboo! I was outside and some nice people saw that I was hurt and they took me to the Pussycat Doctor. The Dr. fixed my paw right up and I am so grateful! I'm feeling so much better and what I'd love to do right now is to GO HOME, only I don't know where that is. I'm hoping that you want to keep me forever and ever. It's time for me to start my life over! I can be a little cranky at times but do enjoy humans company when it is convenient for me.  When I was at the vet I tested positive for FIV, but I'm not bothered by a few little letters. I feel great, and I can't spell, so that doesn't bother me one bit! I intend to live a rich and full life. Let the humans know you're interested in keeping me safe by going to TAILS OF HOPE at www.tailsofhopenj.com and filling out an application for the Amazing Stewart!

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Tucker is a super handsome 3 year old love bug! He was adopted as a puppy but unfortunately as he aged, he did not do so well with the children in the home so he is now back with us at Eleventh Hour! Tucker needs an adult only home (or with older kids) who understand when to give a dog his space. Tucker has given us nothing but love and affection at the kennel so he proved to us how sweet he can be.  He isn’t a huge fan of dogs but he DOES get along with CATS. He is currently in foster care with TWELVE CATS! Tucker lived with a female puppy (11 months old) but he did not like her too much. We believe he may be good with a calm, submissive female, or best as an only dog. 
He is would be a great fit for a quieter low-traffic household.

If you are interested in Tucker, please visit EHDOGS.ORG to fill out an application and be sure to mention TUCKER (DAX ALABAMA)!!!

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Whiskey originates all the way from Kansas City! She landed herself on the euthanasia list at an overwhelmed shelter and DRM stepped in to rescue her. 

Whiskey is a special girl who has some anxiety, which is controlled with inexpensive meds and she is comfortable in her foster home where she has the structure she needs to thrive. Her foster family and DRM have devoted to keep Whiskey in the program where she will be cared and loved for the rest of her life. There is nothing in the world that Whiskey loves more than her Kong, so if you can, send some her way!

This fabulous foster is a Doberman Rescue Minnesota foster dog.

Please read all adoption steps and policies carefully on our website. http://dobermanrescueminnesota.com/adoption-steps/

Qualified adopters are within the approved adoption area, and Adopter will be requested to visit this foster dog at the foster family home. Our foster families are generally located within a 250 mile radius of Minneapolis, MN.

All DRM dogs are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, health checked, microchipped, dewormed, 4DX tested, and on monthly flea/tick and heartworm prevention.

attributes.descriptionHtml: This is Maverick, a full American Bulldog who's such a LOVER BOY! He LOVES EVERYONE. He's great with all people and meeting strangers out and about. You'll be in danger of some serious snuggles with this boy. Maverick has had a LOT of TRAINING and his OBEDIENCE IS GREAT! He has been though a full BOARD and TRAIN program and KNOWS SIT, STAY, PLACE on his bed UNTIL RELEASED, DOWN, and COME. HE is CRATE TRAINED and WALKS at a great HEEL. Mavericks OBEDIENCE is GREAT. Maverick has lived with another dog, but the other dog wasn't nice to him and he needs a new home where he will be safe from harm and not feel threatened. For this reason, we want to place Maverick in an easy going, loving home where he will thrive with routine and predictability. He currently LIVES with CHILDREN and has been GREAT! He remains a FANTASTIC dog even while being targeted by the other dog. Maverick deserves his time of being the focus dog where he is the apple of his people's eye. He would be so full of smiles, wiggle butts for walks and treats. He is just waiting for someone to love him and share all the love he has to give. He is starving for his forever home that's all his own. We want to place him as an only dog and in return, he'll give you the love of a hundred dogs. Come Meet Maverick. He will own your heart. Contact Cindy at 714-715-5862

attributes.descriptionHtml:
I was rescued from the pound in miserable condition but my foster mum has showered me with love and attention ever since, and has been working with me tirelessly to make me into the sweet and loving girl I am today. I enjoy my walks and love to give you kisses! I am also playful and skilled – I can balance things on my head! I love playing fetch non-stop with my ball, but most of all I love, love, love playing with the water hose where I can jump high in the air! I am very good on a leash with healing and staying with my person. Oh, and I love to be groomed – brush me and I will adore you forever! There’s one thing I don’t handle all too well, and that is surprises. I do love company and get excited when I see friends but initially, I need a slow introduction to new people. All in all, I am pretty predictable – my foster mum will tell you all about it if you decide to open your home and heart to me!

[Panda weighs 55 lbs.]

(1706)

Our website is updated daily

Frankie Mae is spayed, UTD on vaccines and tested negative for FIV/FeLV. Approx. DOB is Sept. 2016.

Meet Frankie Mae- a pretty little tabby with gorgeous green eyes! Frankie May is a fun-loving girl who enjoys playing and exploring her cat tree. Though she is still a young girl, Frankie May is calm and laid-back.

She also enjoys lounging in the sun and looking out the window at the birds. She loves having someone to sleep next to. She sticks close to her humans, helping out with important tasks like working on the computer. She also loves her daily treats - she will do anything for Temptations! 

Frankie wouldn’t mind being your one and only, but would be okay with another laid-back cat.

If interested in adopting Frankie Mae, please fill out an application online at http://nar.rescuegroups.org.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
This is sweet Coco and she's a happy girl who loves to give kisses. She's a Pitbull/Labrador mix with a beautiful mocha colored coat. She weighs 62 pounds, and has a short, stocky build. She has the most adorable floppy ears that are so soft to the touch! She dreams of a calm, relaxed life with good, loving people.  She needs a home without small children because their energy makes her uneasy. She's good company for calm dogs, medium to large size. She's more of a companion for other dogs than a playmate.

Coco is a softie when it comes to her "babies". She likes to carry around a stuffed animal with her.  She really loves all toys and plays well alone.  She enjoys peaceful naps on the hammock, leisurely walks and just hanging around the house with her friends.

Take a look into Coco's gorgeous eyes and consider making room in your heart and home for her. She is waiting for you, and we would love to make that connection. The first step is to email placement@duckteam6.org if you are interested in making her a member of your family. Coco is spayed, microchipped and fully vaccinated.  She is also potty trained, leash and crate trained.  She’s ready to have a family of her own and will make an amazing companion.

DOB est 6/1/2012...   Junior is a SUPER sweet boy.  He came from a hoarder situation where the cats lived in a basement for years with no litter boxes and one light bulb.  In spite of that situation they were very healthy and friendly.  Junior is laid back and friendly.  Junior craves your attention.  Be careful as he insists on rubbing your legs and could trip you up.  He loves to be petted on.  Junior is a lap cat.  Despite not having litter boxes most of his life he has never had an issue using the litter box since being in foster care.  Where he came from the people loved on him so he is very affectionate.  He has not had any health issues since being in foster care as of February 2017.  Junior was one of the first cats rescued the first day we went to the hoarder situation.  He has never looked back.
attributes.name: JUNIOR

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Name: Birdo
Age: 4/17/17
Gender: Female
Breed: Anatolian x
Weight: 85
Dog friendly: Yes
Cat friendly: TBD
Kid friendly: Yes, 10+
House Trained: Yes
Crate Trained: Yes but doesn't need to be
Energy level: Moderate
History: Pulled from an animal control
Adoption Fee: $500.00

 

From the Foster: 

I have known Laika (Formally known as Birdo) and her prior owners since puppyhood.  She had to be returned to rescue through no fault of her own, and I am happy to act as her foster home now to find her the best forever family.   She loves to play with our resident dog. Even though she is twice his size she rarely overpowers him. 

 

She is house and crate trained, however I have not had her in a crate at all. No accidents in the house ever. 

 

She is well behaved when left alone in the house except for barking at sights and sounds outside. We are working on this, however, it can be alleviated if she can be in an area where she cannot see outside the window. 

 

She does not like strangers but will warm up to them after period of time where she can observe them and get used to their presence. 

 

She requires a home that does not have small children. Age 10 and above are fine as long as they are educated to be her kind and gentle leader.

 

Anatolian shepherd is a guardian breed and as such she is inclined to guard any space that she is in including her backyard. We are working on training her to accept that the next-door neighbors are OK to be in their own yard and not to bark at them. 

 

She would love a home that has a spacious fenced in yard where she can be outside for long periods of time while her people are home. She has a heavy winter coat and loves to stay outside in the winter for hours at a time. Her previous owner would snow blow the snow into a mountain for her to sit atop in the backyard.

 

She loves to touch base with her people with brief cuddle sessions, but otherwise prefers to relax in a separate space. 

 

She is anxious when in new surroundings, which results in a lack of appetite and may seem confused about what she is supposed to do. Patience and gentle guidance will get her through it. After about 4 weeks here, she has a normal appetite and has learned our daily routine. She likes to be in whatever room you are in. She responds more readily, to “no bark” and “come”, though not perfectly. She is not food and treats oriented so patience and consistent follow-through are the key to training her. 

 

She is ultimately a sweet dog and GREAT companion

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Kona's story: Kona came to the Stafford SPCA back in 2017 as a tiny kitten. For the past three years she had been living in her home. Up until recently, things had been going great, until a dog was brought into the home and they were not a good match. Kona loves to be held like a baby, getting chin scratches and having nice perch to look out of the window and watch the birds and squirrels!

Kona is our current office kitty, as she can be a bit of a bully to others. She loves all the attention she gets from staff in the office. Some of her favorite things to do are walk on top of the cubicle walls around the office to say "hello!" to everyone, try and catch skins, and sleeps in the middle of the floor where everyone is trying to walk. She also cannot drink water with out getting it all over her face. She is quite the character!  

 

Are you the perfect forever home for Kona?

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Rescue date  6/15/17
SHELBY is a cute little PUREBRED Chihuahua who is about 4 years. old and weighs 9 lbs. She was one of several dogs who were rescued from the backyard of someone who was unable to provide them with proper care. She loves other dogs but is a bit on the unsure side when interacting with humans. She's a sweet girl who just needs to continue working on building her confidence. She is best suited for a quiet adult family in which someone can be with her throughout most of the day. Having a well-adjusted companion dog to follow and learn from would be extremely helpful to her as well. She just needs someone to believe in her and help her to blossom into the happy, confident little fur-kid who she deserves to be. The Adoption Fee for SHELBY is $225 and includes spay, up-to-date vaccines, and microchip with registration. Please NOTE that she is AVAILABLE for ADOPTION in CA ONLY! Please understand also that we are a non-profit organization that operates on a small number of volunteers. We are, therefore, UNABLE to ACCEPT PHONE CALLS at this time. If you'd like more information about SHELBY, please send an EMAIL to us at www.saveasmalldogrescue@gmail.com. To submit an online ADOPTION APPLICATION, please go to the SASDR website at www.saveasmalldogrescue.org. We receive numerous applications. If you are among the finalists in the selection process for SHELBY, you will be contacted by phone from SASDR for a phone visit. If you are not available at the time of our call, we will leave a message that includes a time at which we will try later to reach you. SASDR is located in Phelan, CA (San Bernardino County in southern CA). ThanksWe are located in the High Desert, Phelan, next to Victorville and Hesperia.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Kabuki enjoys attention on her terms, she likes to wrap herself around your feet and loves ear scratches. She enjoys playing with her bell and laying on her cat tower. She does prefer a quiet, calm environment to herself, preferably without cats, dogs or small children. Kabuki has hypertrophic cardiomyopathy and will need monthly medication but she is definitely worth it.

No out of state adoptions.

To apply to adopt this pet please fill out a Preliminary Adoption Application at http://streetpaws.org/adoption-application/. This application does not commit you to an adoption. It is used to screen those interested to make sure the home is a good match for the pet. We verify vet history on current/previous pets to ensure pets have been spayed/neutered and vaccinated annually. Our adoption fee is $100 for all of our cats. They have been given age-appropriate vaccinations, are spayed/neutered, feline leukemia and feline aids tested, dewormed, have received flea prevention and micro-chipped.

No kids, cats, does best with playful female dogs his size.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Carlos is a beautiful boy that LOVES to be brushed. It's difficult, though, because he's so busy trying to rub against his foster mom. He purrs like a pro, has a great appetite and sometimes plays with toys.

After 5 years, Carlos was returned to Stray H.E.L.P. through no fault of his own. He is loving, affectionate and quite charming. He developed urinary crystals and needed medical help which the family was unable to provide him. We have done a full blood work up, urinary testing and exam. He has gotten a completely clean bill of health. He loves his UR prescription diet which completely manages his condition and he has no other known medical issues. He has a heart murmur, however, with further testing it has been determined there is no threat to the functioning of the heart.

We estimate his birthdate to be 03/20/2016. He was rescued in Wingdale, NY as part of a trap/neuter/return or place effort along with his family.

Our required adoption donation is $150 per kitten or $125 per cat (older than 9 months). All our rescues are up to date on shots, microchipped, tested for FIV/FeLV/Heartworm. They are dewormed, treated for parasites and free of fleas. Each is spayed or neutered and given a rabies vaccination. 

An application must be completed to be considered to adopt from Stray HELP. You can download it from HERE OR directly ONLINE If your application is approved we conduct a home visit for final approval of adoption. To view more pictures of cats and kittens in our program visit us on FaceBook.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Hello! My name is Sasha. I am a pretty independent mellow lady. I was rescued from my owners that were going to shoot me. Why? They decided because I like to keep to myself there is no reason to keep me alive. I just need a quiet home where someone will just let me be me. I would love a nice sunny spot for relaxing. I do like affection just typically in small amounts. My previous owners let me free feed so I got quite overweight. I am working on my figure but I will need to keep at it for quite some time. Someone has to have a spot for me so I can get healthy and be cared for. 

Date of birth (estimated): 7/29/2009

Good with Dogs: Tolerant

Good with Cats: Tolerant

House Trained: yes

Adoption Fee:   $90

 

 

If you are interested in meeting or adopting this animal, please read the following before submitting an adoption application on our website - fureverhomerescue.com.

Adoption fee includes spay/neuter, microchip, age appropriate vaccinations, Feline Leukemia & FIV testing & de-worming.  We ask that our cats remain indoor cats unless otherwise stated & agreed upon & do not allow declawing -click here if you would like to learn more about why we do not support declawing.   We are a smaller group that typically takes on harder cases that require special homes so we ask that applicants live in our area - if you do not live in the MN or surrounding states, please contact us via email before submitting an application to determine whether the animal you are interested in is a case we are comfortable adopting out to a family out of our area.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Atlas is ready to be the king of your world! This handsome young bridle boy is around 3.5 years old and happiest when he's running and playing fetch.  Atlas is well trained and knows how to sit, shake, stay, lay down, wait, come, leave it and get up. Atlas is also muzzle trained, he prefers to wear this when meeting strangers or doing scary things like visiting the vet's office. 

Atlas would thrive in an active home with adults only who are dog savvy and maintain a relatively quiet home life. We don't know all of his background, but we know that strangers in the home are scary to Atlas and he isn't sure if he's supposed to protect you from them or not!  Atlas loves to play, so another playful dog in the home would make for a perfect match! Atlas is kennel and potty trained, and also loves to give kisses. A 4-6 foot high fenced in yard would be a dream come true for ol' Atlas, here he could run and play to his hearts content and maybe learn some more impressive commands with a little help from his new family.

If you are interested in learning more about Atlas please complete an adoption application for consideration at www.AdoptHope.org.  The adoption fee for Atlas is $250 and includes his neuter, microchip, current vaccinations and preventatives as well as a FREE obedience class through Cedar Run in Hiawatha.  Our adoption process includes reference and background checks, a vet check and home visit.
attributes.name: Atlas

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Meet MJ! He is a 9yr old beagle/terrier mix. He was found as a stray in KY and ended up in a kill shelter...until we rescued him. He seems to get along with every other dog we have (incl puppies of all ages). He walks well on a leash once he gets over the excitement of being out with you. At only about 40 lbs, he is the perfect sized companion dog. MJ is very smart too and learned to sit for a treat & give his paw within 5mins. His aim is to please :) We find that he doesn't like to be without people in general but that's not to say that he likes all people and is definately picky about who he trusts. The ideal home would have someone around rather than leaving him for the workday and would have some dog training knowledge about how to handle a fear aggressive dog. We can no longer bring him to adoption events since many in the general public do not know how to read a dog's body language (he does give signs when he's uncomfortable). We would recommend a low-traffic household for sure because of the potential fear aggressive bite and someone with experience in dealing with this behavior.

Our adoption fee is $325 and all of our pets come with full vet records.  All animals are up to date on vaccinations & dewormed.  Unless otherwise indicated, puppies are NOT spayed or neutered since our vet recommends waiting until 6mos of age to do so.  Please keep in mind we are a Rescue Group and most of our pups come to us with little or no background info regarding breed, eventual size, age or prior health issues. We rely on the expertise of our veterinarians and make estimates based on past experience. Also, when you're adopting from a Rescue, you should ask questions! You should always get shot/medication records and the rescue should have had the dog for a bit of time to check for disease. Take the time to educate yourself before adopting. A reputable rescue will have nothing to hide and will answer ALL your questions!!!Please visit our Web Site to see all of the pets we have for adoption. Our site contains information about our adoption process and fees, our application, and answers to frequently asked questions. Please read it carefully before contacting us. If you are interested in adopting THIS wonderful pet, we strongly encourage you to complete our adoption application now. Once we receive and approve your application, we will notify you of approval. The first application to be received and approved will get 1st choice - be sure that your references are available and willing to speak with us. Thank You Visit us at one of our next adoption days.  Details are on our site under the "How to Adopt" tab. Hope to see you there!

Snowflake is a loveable and affectionate 10 yr old girl who is a total house dog, just wanting to be inside with her family as a companion and protecter. She is a happy girl with a tail that curls prettily over her back and wags happily when she sees her person, a leash or food bowl. She loves morning and evening walks.  She gets along with other dogs and can be bouncy and playful with them but would be content as either an only dog or with another dog her own size. She is house trained, crate trained and respectful of property. She is very mellow overall but can get crotchety with young dogs who are disrespectful. She knows her basic commands and walks well on leash with a training collar. Snowflake loves playing in the yard, car rides and running errands with her person. She is a perfect companion dog who is non-intrusive when you are busy. She has not been around children so would do best in an adult home without cats.

If you are interested in meeting any of our dogs please complete an adoption or foster application on our website at  www.happyheartsgsr.org .  Also please follow us and get the latest updates on our dogs on facebook at  www.facebook.com/HappyHeartsGSDRescue .

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Here at Adopt-A-Dog, Fry serves the role of class goofball very well. Effusive in both his love for his friends and in every experience he has, Fry is one of a kind. He takes to new experiences, such as learning how to play soccer or football, or going for a ride in the Adopt-A-Dog van, with an enthusiasm that cannot be matched. He truly is a unique dog and has most of his human friends saying "Oh, Fry!" or "That's Fry for you" whenever he does something just a bit more awkward than his counterparts.

A big guy, Fry came to our shelter when his original family could not handle his size. At the time, he had not reached a year old so he still had both growing and learning to do. We began working with Fry on basic obedience and his manners when it came to both people and other dogs. The Fry we have today has come a long way from the Fry we first met, and we know he is ready to show off for his very own family. When making new friends, Fry typically needs a bit more time to get comfortable and get to know someone. Once he has spent some time with you, and has been feed a copious amount of treats, Fry will be your best bud. 

 All this big guy needs in a home is a willingness to get slobbered on followed by tons of comfortable places to sleep and stretch out. We know that this not-so-small Fry is ready for his new family. 

For more information, please contact us at (914) 273-1674 or adoptions@adoptadog.org.

 If you are interested in adopting Fry or any of our other adoptable dogs, please fill out the following online application here:  

https://forms.gle/pnkaGTG8Cy4dgQRJ8

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Bobby's mom is a Great Pyrenees/Maremma who has spent her life as a working livestock guardian dog, first in Kansas and later in Texas. Bobby was raised with goats, and had some exposure to chickens, but always seemed more interested in playing with the other dogs than in protecting the livestock. We moved him into the house for some basic training, such as how to walk on a leash, as well as crate-training and house/potty-training. He also got a refresher course in good manners around chickens. He did really well with all of these changes, but didn't really seem HAPPY in the house, so we moved him into one of our paddocks. Bobby seems happier living outside, but will come in the house if that's what you ask. He has good guardian instincts as far as walking the perimeter and barking when he hears coyotes. We think the best home for Bobby might be as a family guardian on a small homestead, where he can live outside, but be allowed to come inside during thunderstorms, which frighten him. He is very shy on meeting new people, so he needs an adopter with the patience to earn his trust. He also needs secure fencing that is at least 5' tall. He hasn't challenged the fencing at Windsong Ranch, but because of his skittishness with strangers, we don't feel safe putting him in a new home with fencing shorter than 5'. Once a fearful dog goes over the fence, it can be almost impossible to get them home again.

If Bobby looks like just the companion you need in your life, please submit your application at www.bluebonnetrescue.org.

attributes.descriptionHtml: My name is Diva and I am a special blind girl. My other senses are keen so don't think you are pulling a fast one over on me! I am spayed ...so we got that out of the way early. I am housetrained and crate trained...so that should give me extra points. I am good with children and if they try and pull my ears I won't be a happy girl. Actually children and me are great together, I am not good with dogs and cats because I don't like those kinds of surprises. I was a surrender due to landlord issues and I would've paid the rent on time but I couldn't find the checkbook. I was frightened beyond belief and confused having been in the shelter. Through all of this I was still a sweetheart to everybody. I love meeting new people and they feel the same way. I had been living with a family for seven years including children. I do really well in my foster and when I get used to the lay of the land I am great...and I don't own a GPS. I am 9 yrs old and I weigh 55 lbs....and I guess I look pretty good even though I can't see for myself in the mirror. I am a special girl and if anybody would find it in their heart to adopt me I would be the happiest girl in the world. I would add something very special in your life that you would remember forever. Thanks for checking in on me and caring. My application is at oneloveanimalrescue.org

attributes.descriptionHtml: Covina is such a friendly and pretty girl! Her cheerful bunny dances are so much fun to watch. She has beautiful black eyeliner and such pretty two tone ears. Covina will do well with any kind family. Covina would make a great companion to a neutered bunny boy after a proper introduction, She is potty trained and uses the litter box. She is accustomed to living with cats and is used to gentle dogs. She is shy with new people so will do best with older, gentle children. She will do best indoors with the family in a roomy xpen or wire dog crate with plenty of run time in a bunny proofed area. Covina has megacolon. Sometimes her poops are misshapen. She manages this very well but we will be careful that her new family is willing to monitor this. She should do well in a home willing to limit sugary treats and feed her lots of fresh hay and limited pellets. You can email jmclaug@me.com to get more information on Covina and to adopt her

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Personality:   Miss Reagan appreciates a more quiet, one on one environment. She is quite a snuggler and will take in all the loving and attention you want to dole out. Don't be fooled by that though because she can be an escape artist and will not go to a home with a chain link fence. It's best she have a 6 foot privacy fence or no fence at all with leash walks. She will do great as the only dog or maybe with a buddy but that buddy will not be a cat or any other small breed or prey. She is a confirmed cat killer. Spunky Girl when she wants to be but is great inside and settles down beautifully.

None of our foster dogs are tested with cats because we have no way of testing them with cats. Siberians are notorious for their high prey drive and typically kill cats, rabbits, chickens, birds, squirrels, opossums, etc., so we don't have much success adopting them out to homes with cats. Most of our foster dogs are with us for killing cats, chickens and goats to begin with so our assumption is they are not good with cats and other small things that move. 

Siberians are typically good with children of all ages and the only reason we would not list them as not good with kids is because they may be too energetic and bouncy and knock over a toddler.

Southern Siberian Rescue is a volunteer based 501(c)3 organization based out of Raleigh, NC, so we do not have a physical facility with operating hours that you can visit to meet our dogs. All of our foster dogs are in our personal homes. You need to fill out our adoption application (http://www.southernsiberian.com/info/adoption) and get approved to adopt and then we will set a time for you to meet our foster dogs. As a volunteer based group, we all have jobs, family, personal dogs and other commitments but we try to acknowledge and process applications as quickly as we can. That being said, we try to keep our available foster dogs as current as we can also but it is time consuming to get pics and information on new dogs so not all of our dogs are listed at all times. Please fill out our application and then we can discuss dogs that will work for you and your situation. We average 40-45 Siberians in our program so we are certain we have one that will work for you. Please know that we are not obligated to answer inquiries on dogs as we will focus on approved applicants. Again, there is ample time to discuss all of our foster dogs AFTER we have an approved application on file. We do adopt out of state as long as we can get a home check done. We ask that you, your family and existing pets make the trip to NC to meet and adopt our foster dogs. 

SSR can not and will not hold dogs for anyone. If we do, that means another Siberian will die in a shelter because a shelter dogs time is very limited, as is our foster space. We do our best to process applications in the order received and first application gets first interest in our foster dog(s). We understand that there will be scheduling conflicts with home checks and meet and greets but we will try to accommodate for that if a potential adopter has interest in a particular foster dog in our program.

All Southern Siberian Rescue foster dogs are microchipped, up to date on shots, spay/neutered, on monthly heartworm preventative and flea and tick preventative. For additional information on Southern Siberian Rescue and Siberian Huskies, please visit www.SouthernSiberian.com.

To fill out an application, please visit http://www.southernsiberian.com/info/adoption

attributes.descriptionHtml: Sheba is a lovely 9 yr old, 60lb Bulldog who came to rescue from a breeding farm. She suffered from a painful condition known as entropian, where her eyelids curled inwards making each blink of her eyes miserable. She also had a large hernia as a result of years of repeated pregnancys and C-sections. She also had to have a dental, to remove a couple of infected teeth. Now recovered and doing well, she is looking for a furrever home to spend her golden years. She gets very bonded to her person and will cry when she can  not be near them, so no apartments/attached dwelling type homes. She will need a Bulldog experienced home with no other pets. No children please, no exceptions.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Hi … my name is Sebastian and here are some things you need to know about me:

All dogs are special ... some of God's finest creations, and then there are those who need very special heroes to help them live their best lives. Can you be Sebastian's hero?

Sweet Sebastian … what a little mystery he is.  Per the previous owner, his mom is a Boston Terrier and dad is a Chihuahua … which explains the gorgeous brindle coat, the underbite, the big ears and the goofy personality. 

He is such a puzzle because once he trusts you, you see a different pup, but until he decides to let you into his world, he is afraid of everything and he tries to hide. He is very cautious of human touch and does not want anyone to pick him up.  He will jump into your lap when he is ready, but he still does not want even his best human friend to pick him up.  And if pushed too quickly, he will warn with a low growl.  He seems to be partial to women, although he does fine with his foster dad.  We are trying to untangle all the pieces of his puzzle to make his world a happier place.

Sebastian needs a special home with a patient family!  He will do best with a family with doggy experience … not a good choice for a first pet.  This little boy is truly a diamond-in-the-ruff.  A big investment of time and patience in him will be sure to reap great rewards.

If you do not feel like you can adopt and meet his special needs, you can still help him by sponsoring his extended care with tax-deductible donations.  A one-time donation, or monthly or quarterly donations designated for Sebastian's care will be appreciated.

Approximate age/birthdate:  born July 22, 2014

Weight/size: ~14 lbs

Housebroken:  YES (if you do your part and take him out regularly)

Crate trained:  YES

Personality:  very cautious, timid, slow to warm up, but sweet and loving once he does, a bit cautious of human touch until he knows he can trust

Energy level:  medium 

Fenced yard required?:   YES – due to the fact that he is very skittish, he tends to be in ‘flight’ mode so he must have a physical fence for his own safety … no exceptions

Does he/she jump fences?  NO

Leash walk:  YES (be cautious and use a secure harness and a sturdy leash)
 
Obedience training:  NO

Riding in vehicles:  RIDES OK … gets a little stressed at first but settles quickly

Spayed/neutered:   YES

Up-to-date on routine vaccinations:   YES

Microchipped:   YES

Social with other dogs:  YES

Social with cats:  Has not been around cats

Good with children:  He might eventually be OK with older, calm children but any excessive noise and activity makes him really nervous and he wants to hide.

Adoption donation:  $175

If you think Sebastian might be the perfect pup for you, please go to www.allamericanmuttrescue.org/forms and complete your adoption application online.

We are an all-volunteer group, so please be patient and understand that it takes an average of 7-14 days to process the applications including reference checks, follow-up questions and home visits.  You can expedite the process by providing accurate email addresses for all your references.  Time to make phone calls is limited and we often have multiple applications in process.  We make every effort to move through them as quickly as possible.

When your application is approved, we will schedule a meet-and-greet to see if Sebastian picks you too.

If it seems that the adoption will be a good match for all, there is an adoption fee, and an adoption contract to be signed.

Please feel free to email weluvpups@hotmail.com if you have additional questions.
attributes.descriptionText:
Hi … my name is Sebastian and here are some things you need to know about me:All dogs are special ... some of God's finest creations, and then there are those who need very special heroes to help them live their best lives. Can you be Sebastian's hero?Sweet Sebastian … what a little mystery he is.  Per the previous owner, his mom is a Boston Terrier and dad is a Chihuahua … which explains the gorgeous brindle coat, the underbite, the big ears and the goofy personality.  He is such a puzzle because once he trusts you, you see a different pup, but until he decides to let you into his world, he is afraid of everything and he tries to hide. He is very cautious of human touch and does not want anyone to pick him up.  He will jump into your lap when he is ready, but he still does not want even his best human friend to pick him up.  And if pushed too quickly, he will warn with a low growl.  He seems to be partial to women, although he does fine with his foster dad.  We are trying to untangle all the pieces of his puzzle to make his world a happier place.
Sebastian needs a special home with a patient family!  He will do best with a family with doggy experience … not a good choice for a first pet.  This little boy is truly a diamond-in-the-ruff.  A big investment of time and patience in him will be sure to reap great rewards.If you do not feel like you can adopt and meet his special needs, you can still help him by sponsoring his extended care with tax-deductible donations.  A one-time donation, or monthly or quarterly donations designated for Sebastian's care will be appreciated.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Meet beautiful Pansie! She is a Pit Bull mix who was born in 2014 and weighs about 40 pounds. She was rescued off the streets of Texas with a horrific case of mange. This poor baby was a sight for sore eyes, she hardly had any hair left and her skin was raw and infected. We made sure she got immediate medical care and Pansie is doing awesome now! Her fur has almost grown back completely but it may take awhile longer to get her coat back to 100% because of how severe her condition originally was.  She is spayed, up to date on vaccines, and is great with people of all ages and does well with other dogs with slow intros. Her foster mom says that she loves her people very much and is so sweet! She would do well in a home with slow intro to other dogs or could live as an only dog as she loves affection from humans. Pansie is house trained, crate trained, loves toys to chew on, enjoys walks and car rides, and is wonderful with kids! Pansie is long overdue for her happy ever after and we are rooting for this sweetheart big time! She deserves so much more than the life of neglect that she had to suffer through for so long. If you would like to make Pansie the newest member of your family and love of your life, please fill out an adoption application here: http://www.rescuedogsrocknyc.org/general-application 

RDR's adoption fees include the cost of spay/neuter/microchip at an RDR-approved facility, whether completed before adoption or if deferred because the pet is too young or has a medical issue.  All pets are also current on age-appropriate vaccines at the time of adoption.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Date into Rescue: 8/23/2017

Reason for being in rescue: Stray- nc shelter
Foster location: Dreamweaver Farms, Pacolet SC
Special Needs? Ollie has no known medical issues but is very strong willed.  He despises other dogs and cats and needs to be in a home where he does not have contact with other canines or cats. He will attack other dogs.  It is sad because he was not like this originally but something changed.  
Weight: 46 lbs
Height: 21" at the shoulder

Adoption Fee: $200

Fence needed? Secure fence - prefer privacy please or a back yard that does not back up to a yard with a dog so he can play and not worry about the other dogs.  

What kind of home would be best for me? Hmmm.. I'm really not hard to please. Just give me attention and let me lay around on the couch with you!  I love people, I love living in a house and I love being part of your life.  I am a lot of dog - you won't need another one if you have me.  

Ollie is going to be amazing in the right hands.  Our owner experince level for Ollie is an  8 - More than 10 years as dog owner and preferrably with a terrier breed. Has taken at least three professional training courses. Long history of superior vet care. No history of rehoming or rehoming only for serious lifestyle challenge, worked through reputable rescue to place and follows up.  

What is my personality like?  I'm Ollie Beckett and if my name wasn't already cute enough.. just look at my sweet face. I was found a stray in North Carolina and taken to a local shelter. I was actually just saved in the nick of time... I was making my way to be sent to doggie heaven until the lady walking me to "the room" saw my tail wag and it was all over from there. She begged and of course CPR said yes! 

I'm a silly boy that loves all humans. I can't possibly give out enough hugs for everyone around here. I will love you through the good times, and bad times. I will be your best friend through it all, given the chance. I walk well on a leash but I love love love sniffing everything I can so please let's make some walks slow walks.  I don't know any basic commands yet but I bet I could learn. One of my favorite things to do is roll around on the couch and nuzzle under every blanket I can get under. I love, and I love hard, Please take me home!

Update 6/18- I was returned to the rescue because I did not get along with some dogs that I have met. It was also said that I have separation anxiety and that I have lunged at people/cars going by. So far, the caregivers have not seen this behavior at the rescue either time I have been here.

How do I act when I first meet new people? friendly 

House trained?  Dogs can be house trained if they are in the right environment and are allowed to follow a schedule as long as a physical reason doesn't keep them from being trained.  A dog house trained in my home may not be in yours.  We will help you teach your new dog this necessary skill and based on your schedule.

My age: Estimated birth date 8/24/2016

Welcome to Cats Meow Dogs Bark Rescue, is an all volunteer animal welfare and rescue organization! Animals listed on our websites and other adoptable websites are available for adoption at our adoption house; Pounce & Fetch (512 Southview Blvd South St. Paul, MN 55075), we have no set hours, but we are always there cleaning and caring for the animals that reside at Pounce & Fetch! Please be aware of our sign on our front door. It will ask that you "Please knock, we are here cleaning" when you are more then welcome to come in and help us and visit the animals. Should it read "We are closed" means that we are not ready to receive guests and perhaps call to schedule at time or wait till the sign is flipped.

To start the journey of adopting a new family member from Cats Meow Dogs Bark Rescue you'll need to complete our adoption application. It is the first step toward possibly adding a new member to your family. You can either stop in at Pounce & Fetch to pick up and complete it or email us at adoptablepets@aol.com and we will send you the form, please complete and return via email.  Unanswered question could delay your application. Please don't be intimidated by our Adoption Application, its purpose in genuine. We have kept it simple for a reason so that we can get to know you and your family so that we can assist you with finding the right pet to join your family, forever! Please note that we are an all volunteer animal rescue and welfare organization, and there may be times where we may have to reschedule (several times too) the Meet & Greets, visiting at Pounce & Fetch as well as Home Visits. We so appreciate your understand and patience.

We are excited to assist you in your search and adoption of your new family member! Don't forget we are always seeking donations so that we can help the animals we rescue and save each and everyday! Please donate NOW so we can help them today! 651-888-2469 or 651-343-1964

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Gazing into Kae's soulful amber eyes tells you without words that she is an old soul restored to a vital body. One meaning for 'Kae' is 'keeper of the keys' and having known her for a little while, she has already started gathering the keys to her caregivers' hearts, so we are certain she will collect and treasure the keys to her forever family's hearts quickly as well!

Kae's photo shows her offering the excellent eye contact so important to training success. This focus combined with her eager to please attitude, and all you will need to add are the best possible treats in the whole wide world. Then the sky will be your limit when continuing to build her skills together.

Kae will enjoy a hike on the trail as much as a quiet afternoon lounging in her sunny back yard. She's not one for the hustle and bustle of city life and will thrive on the predictable routines others might find a tad, well, almost boring. 

Kae has a foundation of basic obedience, beginning exposure to agility, early leash skills (tempered by youthful enthusiasm); she is crate trained and housebroken.


Kae would prefer a forever home with a private back yard so she can run and play to her heart's content and rest with limited distractions. Kae can be environmentally sensitive to some loud sounds. If you are interested in learning more details about Kae, please contact:   rorrcanine@gmail.com

attributes.descriptionHtml:
**Foster or Adopter Needed!**

Hi, I'm Trace!! I'm looking for my forever home, any chance you are looking for a big lovable ball of fur? I am 3 years old, and a flat coated collie mix, weighing in at about 100lbs. I am super smart, I know all those basic commands, like sit, stay, and down. However, I also know come here, crate up, off, leave it, and quiet. My daily activities include lounging around taking naps, going for walks and playing fetch. I also really love to play in the water, but only when a human is involved, it's more fun that way. My perfect home would be with someone who is a firm leader. Experienced handler is a bonus! Someone who will keep my daily routine structured and consistent.  I am a little timid at first when meeting new people but man once I know you, I love you forever.  No kids please because they make me nervous, Word on the street is I am a one woman type of guy. 

My adoption fee is $25 locally (out of state $175 including health certificate and transport fee).  I have tested heartworm negative and am  up   to date on all vaccinations, neutered and microchipped.   You can apply at www.soca-fbc.org/adoptables.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
If you've been on the look out for a cuddly, affectionate kitty, look no further! Three and a half year old Zipper is the definition of 'love bug.' While a little shy around strangers, once he gets to know people, he absolutely adores them and believes everyone should adore him, too. Zipper races over for cuddles and pets and snoozes near his fosters while they work, watch TV, or nap. He just wants to be wherever the people are!

Zipper enjoys playing with toys, especially flirt poles and cat nip stuffies. This social boy LOVES the kitty trees in the house and always seems to find a nice perch where he’s close to his fosters while still being high enough to survey his kingdom. Zipper also enjoys overtaking the dog crates for a good snooze or a quiet hang out.

Somewhat shy, Zipper kindly requests that any children in the home be old enough to understand that chasing him is very scary. He does well with the other cats as well as with large dogs. 

Zipper's adoption fee is $125. Check out furangelsas.com/adopt to apply today!

attributes.descriptionHtml: Glen Fry is a German Shephard mix that came to our shelter surrendered with his mother and his sister Winslow Arizona when he was just a puppy.  His starfish volunteer likes to carry him like a baby because… well he lets her and he likes to show the other dogs how much he gets cuddled. Once he is outside he thrives!  He loves to walk on the leash and he warms up pretty quickly (30 minutes and you might be his new best friend).  Glen likes other dogs and has been tested with small dogs and didn’t seem to notice they were playing while he was exploring the play area. He was in the same kennel as his sister for the first two years of his life and if she didn’t decide to tattoo his ear he would still be with her. He misses that companionship in a friend or side kick. He’s such a sweet boy and is looking for his forever home that will help bring out his confidence with a little love and affection. Please come meet Glen Fry!

attributes.descriptionHtml: Little Man has quite the story of abandonment, rescue, adoption, escape, search parties and travel back and forth across the US. To say he is well traveled is an understatement! He is perfect lap size at 15 lbs and gives sweet kisses and loves to be with his human when he's not playing with the others. He is great with all the other dogs in rescue, is house trained and knows the doggy door. He is around 2 years old. He is very quiet and sleeps in his little bed through the night or in the bed with you. It can take him a bit of time to get to know you so some patience is a must. Little Man can climb low fences so privacy fence is the safest. Please consider opening your home and heart to this wonderful little man. Apply at www.krrtx.org/forms. Adoption fee is $170

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Date into Rescue: 9/9/2017

Reason for being in rescue: One of Hurricane Irma's orphans.
Foster location: Dreamweaver Farms, Pacolet SC
Special Needs? None noted
Weight: 65 lb
Height:
Spayed/Neutered: Yes

Adoption Fee: $99

Fence needed? Yes, a high fence he can't climb. He needs room to run! 

What kind of home would be best for me? I would love a home with lots of excercise and playtime, maybe a field to run in and play and at the end of the day when my family and I are all tuckered out we can go lay on a comfy bed in front of a fireplace! Dreams can come true, right? 

What is my personality like? I am nothing but sweet! I'm still getting used to everything around here but considering everything I've been through (hurricane Irma and moving so much during rescue) my caregivers say I'm doing great! I like to howl at the moon when I'm outside at night like a true-to-breed hound and I love to play with people and give hugs! I love to explore, I would make a fabulous tracking dog with the right training. That is what I feel like I'm supposed to do! Sniffing and hunting things down. 

I can be head strong, just like any other stubborn hound dog.. but with the right people I'm working through them. I would prefer to be the only dog since I can be dog selective but I'm not against meeting your 4 legged members to see if I will like them!

How do I act when I first meet new people? I am sweet and loving  a bit shy at first but I warm up to you between snacks and rubbing behind my ears. :)

Other tips and tidbits: Estimated Birthdate: 7/18/2015.  I'm really smart. I am highly treat motivated and know how to sit, hand shake, lay down and when my caregiver said play dead I even rolled over on my back belly up!

House trained? Dogs can be house trained if they are in the right environment and are allowed to follow a schedule as long as a physical reason doesn't keep them from being trained.  A dog house trained in my home may not be in yours.  We will help you teach your new dog this necessary skill and based on your schedule.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Handsome and elegant - that's how they describe Stanley.  Stanley was found as a stray with an old eye injury that doesn't slow him down.  He is very well-trained and completed a board & train program.   Stanley's professional training comes with lifetime follow-ups if needed.

Stanley loves going for rides in the car if you'd like company.  Stanley would do best with an owner that will provide him with structure to which he has become accustomed.  He loves the outdoors and is excellent on-leash. When it comes to other dogs, he seems to prefer female over male dogs. Stanley is up to date on vaccinations, neutered, and microchipped.

If you're interested in meeting Stanley, go to EHRDOGS.ORG and submit an application.  Don't forget to ask for STANLEY MARTIN STEELE!!

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Joy came to us from Texas and we all know that everything is bigger in Texas and and so is her personality.

- Joy is a happy but exciteable dog.
- She is super sweet and loves to cuddle (all the time if you let her).
- Joy gets along well with people but due to her energy level must be in a home with children 6 and up 
- She is house and crate trained.
- Joy does not do well in the car. She gets very excited on car rides as other cars go by (she is trying to chase them). 

- Joy loves going on walks and knows her basic commands. 
- Joy can get along with other dogs but will push herself onto other dogs with dominant gestures which can cause problems if uncontrolled. Unless you are an experienced bully owner we therefore recommend that she is the only dog in the family. 

No dog parks, no cats, no small dogs, no children younger than 6 years.

 Joy has a lot of energy and her three legs do not slow her down. There are no restrictions on what home she should be in. You will need to be able to provide daily exercise for her to keep her energy under control. She can go up and down steps without problems. Joy is all muscle and will jump in the car all by herself. You will be amazed!

We would love to see Joy go into a home with a fenced in yard (4' minimum height). She loves laying outside in the sun during the day.

Joy is in good health otherwise.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
We are working on adoption applications, but may not have a volunteer willing to do any function that includes contact with other individuals until the case count as shown a decrease for 10 consecutive days.  Be patient.

Paws Crossed Dog Rescue Serves the Eastern Panhandle of WV and surrounding communities. Please read "Adoption info" on the left side of our website.

Taco Belle has the typical personality for a chihuahua.  She is very active and could go to a home with or without another dogs.   She attaches herself to her owners and is very local.   She does not like cats as her foster home has one.  Belle likes to bark and chase afterthem.   Belle is a jumper and therefor will need a fenced in yard with supervision .  She is small but very mighty . Once she has attached herself to you, she will love you for life.
 
Taco Belle comes to us from the southern part of WV where she was picked up as a stray.   She had been running for sometime and stopping by several fast food restaurants for her meals.   Taco Bell was her favorite place to stop.  Although she got good meals they could not catch her.  Sadly, she was hit by a car that broke one of her front legs.  We took her in gave her great care and now she is ready for her forever home.


She likes car rides, loves to snuggle under a blanket on your lap. 

Taco Belle is always happy and ready for an adventure.

We don't know how she is with cats.  

Email inquiries can be sent to PawsCrossedDogRescue@yahoo.com

*Experienced owner with veterinary references required* View bio for details ⬇️* 

Surf's up! Malibu Kitty is more fun than a day at the beach! Sunny and warm, Malibu is a sweet little girl. She also loves to have fun and is often found playing with her siblings. Malibu is the most affectionate of her siblings- she loves pets and will roll around and purr in appreciation. 
 
Malibu was found in a cardboard box in a parking lot- along with twelve other kittens! While Malibu is still young, she is past the 'crazy kitten' stage. Well...she does like to chase her tail once in a while, but who doesn't?!

If interested in adopting Malibu, please fill out an application online at http://nar.rescuegroups.org.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Meet Bambalina! This cutie is a 4 year old pointer mix. She’s a happy girl that loves her humans, dog friends, and most importantly her cuddle time. She enjoys playing with toys and other lower energy dogs. Do you like to go for walks and car rides to decompress after a long day? Well so does Bambalina! She can be a little nervous in new situations but warms up quickly especially when she has someone that remains calm and shows her there is nothing to worry about.

Because this sweet girl can be a little nervous living in a mellow environment with kids over 8 who are dog savvy would be best. She is kennel trained and potty trained. If you are the patient, loving family that Bambalina has been waiting for, apply to meet her today at www.rescuerovers.org.

attributes.descriptionHtml: Hi my name is Maddie I'm a blue nose pit mix. I'm about 6-7 years old and I have been in rescue for about 2 years. I was over bread so I'm not too fond of puppies. I do get along with older, calm dogs-I just like my space. I'm better with kids over the age of 9 just because they can be a little to much for me. I would really love a home to call mine! I haven't had the easiest life. I was found running the streets of Phoenix after I escaped a back door breeder where I wasn't taken very good care of. I'm a really good girl!. I like to do is lay on my dog bed and sleep most of the day and I'm really easy to take care of. I just want to be pet at the end of the night when you get home. If you think you could provide that for me, please contact Arf-Anage Dog Rescue to set up a meeting to meet me.

attributes.descriptionHtml: Una is a beautiful black and white kitty who is confident and playful.  She enjoys back rubs and loves petting.  She gets along great with other kitties although she does insist on being in charge, since she is a dominant girl.  Una finds everything you do to be very fascinating and has an endearing quality of draping her arms around everything (water bowl, cat scratcher, etc). She is really good in foster but was adopted and was hiding, swatting and growling at the adopter so she was returned after a week of not eating. She was adopted again and did well until she decided she did not like the resident dog and got defensive again.  For this reason, we will be very selective about the next home she tries.  We think she will do well with a very gentle and calm dog, other playful and confidant cats and a more quiet household.   When meeting new people, she can be shy and will check you out carefully prior to allowing petting, so be prepared.   For more info email jmclaug@me.com

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Sky was born 1/15/2017 and is a Stunning Gray & White Tuxedo girl.

This Beautiful Girl was abandoned with her babies, and was desperately looking for a safe place as the water was rising during Hurricane Harvey.  As she put them on the porch one by one, a kind hearted lady decided to bring them inside her home during the storm.  She contacted us to take them because her landlord said they had to go.

Paws found a wonderful Foster Home for Sky and her babies until they could be available for adoption.  This mother cat was ALWAYS looking out for her three little ones and is now needing a forever family of her own.

Sky is very sweet and loving once she knows you can be trusted.  She is also playful because she is still so young herself.

11/02/2017 Update:  Sky was spayed and microchipped today.  However, we found that her story of being abandoned was not all that happened to her.  She was shot, and not only does the bullet remain close to her spine, we could also see that part of her knee had been shattered, which is why her right leg splays outward.  She also now has spondylosis of L7-S1 vertebrae.  All of this had to be right before the flooding started because she is still healing.  In spite of everything that happened to her, she continued to save and care for her babies!  Sky was an INCREDIBLE MOM!!!  Now that her babies have all found their own home, it is her turn to have a FUREVER Home of her own.

Simon would do best in a home as the only cat as he is a bit of a bully towards some cats.  He is in a foster home but is very independent.  When he wants affection, he'll let you know.  When he wants you to stop, he'll let you know.  He has not been around kids but would probably do ok with teenagers who could understand his personality quirks.  Simon loves laying in the sun and watching the birds outside the window.  If you have a specific question about Simon, you can text his foster mom at 513-967-0007.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
I am a senior with the heart and soul of a puppy. I love to play play play. I love playing with other dogs. I am obedient, house-trained and crate-trained. I pack-walk off-leash and I stay with my pack! I walk nicely on leash with a easy-walk harness. I am 13+ years old. I'm in perfect health. When I get the "play" out of my system, I sleep like a born couch-potato! In other words, I am the perfect dog for an active person or a family with an active person. I require a fenced yard. If I am not an only dog, I must dine at a table for one. So no matter how much I might love my doggy roommates, I want to dine alone. I had an eye removed in the end of 2019. I prefer no surprises on the right side of my body. Speaking before approaching on the right is a good idea so that I'll turn my head and see you. I am charming and a lover. I love back scratches and I'm a world-class kisser. I don't do cats.

Unfortunately, I no longer match my profile from three years ago. Yes, there has not been ONE adoption interest in me in three years. I recently suffered two strokes. I am weak on my right side but I am independent and I still like to play! My cognition is not what it used to be either. I am slower in responding, and I am slow to eat, so my foster mom feeds me by hand. I continue to be house-trained with a doggy door, so my brain injury has not affected my indoor manners.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Quick Facts:
Breed(s): Domestic Medium Hair
Gender: Spayed Female
Age: 3 years
I’m good with: 
Dogs? Unknown    
Cats? Yes    
Kids? No

History:
Tarah hasn't had the best luck so far... originally came to us as a kitten in October of 2017 when her owner could no longer take care of her, she was adopted but then came back to us in December of 2019 when her new family was expecting a new baby. 

Personality:
This spunky diva girl likes to march to the beat of her own drum. Tarah is a very confident self assured kitty who know exactly what she wants out of life. Don't be fooled by her cali-tude all the time though, Tarah has a huge sweet side and if she decides she fancies you she will happily curl up on your lap for hours, purring the whole time. She would make a great kitty companion as long as you respect and understand that she's an independent lady who will happily seek you out when she wants your attention. Tarah isn't a huge fan of her fellow cat roommates but has lived happily with a few other cats in the past. 

Medical:
Tarah is a stunning FeLV+ kitty, our staff is happy to answer any questions you have about bringing an FeLV+ cat into your family. Tarah also has some Feline OCD behavior when stressed and is on a supplement to help keep her calm.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Thor (aka Jermaine) is one of the 'Jackson 5' siblings born in 2017. This handsome boy sadly finds himself without a home once again because his adopter dumped him. Thor is about 50 pounds now. He isn't a fan of being home alone all day, and would do best in a calm, structured home in a quiet location with a patient owner and companion dogs to help him continue to build his confidence. He knows his basic commands like 'sit' and 'stay'. Thor can be timid around new people, but is very sweet when he learns to trust. He is agile and can jump a fence, so a lead when with him in the yard is a must. If you are interested in adopting Thor (aka Jermaine), please put your application in here: http://www.rescuedogsrocknyc.org

 
RDR's adoption fees include the cost of spay/neuter/microchip at an RDR-approved facility, whether completed before adoption or if deferred because the pet is too young or has a medical issue.  All pets are also current on age-appropriate vaccines at the time of adoption.
 
Given technical constraints on this database, this pet's location may not be as listed here. We can, however, provide transport support for pets in foster at a considerable distance from the adopter.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Meet Hamlet! Hamlet is a beautiful 3 yr old male kitty who is looking for a forever family. He is a wonderful family guy and would be fine with kids and other cats. He can't wait to purr his way into your heart. 

The adoption fee of $100 will include spay/neuter, microchip, age appropriate/required vaccinations and any other necessary medical treatment to assure a healthy new cat for your family. Although we make the best guess on the breed of our cats, because they come from shelters, we can never be completely certain of the genetic makeup of the cat. All we can tell you for sure is that they are 100% RESCUED! If you are interested in adopting, please visit our website at www.starfishanimalrescue.com. Once you complete and submit your cat adoption application we will set up an appointment to meet this cat! Thank you for wanting to adopt a Starfish Animal Rescue Kitten! Learn more about us, our mission, and our volunteer opportunities on our Facebook page https://www.facebook.com/sta
